One categorical and one quantitative variable
========================================================
transition: none

Mother's race and infant birth weight in grams

```{r}
df_onecat_onequant <- birthwt %>%
    transmute(race = factor(as.character(race),
                            labels = c("White", "Black", "Other")),
              bwt = bwt) %>%
    tbl_df()

df_onecat_onequant
```


One categorical and one quantitative variable
========================================================
transition: none

* Side-by-side boxplot

```{r}
ggplot(df_onecat_onequant, aes(x = race, y = bwt)) +
    geom_boxplot() +
    xlab("Race") +
    ylab("Birth Weight (gm)\n") +
    theme(axis.title.x = element_text(size = 32),
          axis.text.x  = element_text(size = 24)) +
    theme(axis.title.y = element_text(vjust = 1, size = 32),
          axis.text.y  = element_text(size = 16))
```


One categorical and one quantitative variable
========================================================
transition: none

* Stacked histogram (okay)

```{r}
ggplot(df_onecat_onequant, aes(x = bwt)) +
    geom_histogram(binwidth = 200,
                   color = "black",
                   fill = "white") +
    facet_grid(race ~ .) +
    xlab("Birth Weight (gm)") +
    ylab("Count") +
    theme(strip.text.y = element_text(size = 24)) +
    theme(panel.margin = unit(18, "points")) +
    theme(axis.title.x = element_text(size = 32),
          axis.text.x  = element_text(size = 24)) +
    theme(axis.title.y = element_text(size = 32),
          axis.text.y  = element_text(size = 16))
```


One categorical and one quantitative variable
========================================================
transition: none

* Stacked histogram (better)

```{r}
ggplot(df_onecat_onequant, aes(x = bwt)) +
    geom_histogram(aes(y=(..density..)*200),
                   binwidth = 200,
                   color = "black",
                   fill = "white") +
    facet_grid(race ~ .) +
    xlab("Birth Weight (gm)") +
    ylab("Percent") +
    theme(strip.text.y = element_text(size = 24)) +
    theme(panel.margin = unit(18, "points")) +
    theme(axis.title.x = element_text(size = 32),
          axis.text.x  = element_text(size = 24)) +
    theme(axis.title.y = element_text(size = 32),
          axis.text.y  = element_text(size = 16))
```


